Package me.philcali.device.pool.local

Class LocalDevicePool

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.philcali.device.pool.local.LocalDevicePool
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, DevicePool
    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
@Generated("org.immutables.processor.ProxyProcessor")
@Immutable
public final class LocalDevicePool
extends Object
    A local implementation of a DevicePool. The intention behind this implementation is to facilitate client code integration without requiring a network, ie unit tests. The entire LocalDevicePool is a wrapper around a provision request cache and LocalDevice creation. The LocalDevice implementations are wrappers around the Process and Files APIs.

      • provision

        public ProvisionOutput provision​(ProvisionInput input)
                          throws ProvisioningException
        Creates a provision request for this DevicePool implementation. It is important to know that the provisioning process is asynchronous. Some implementations may be able to fulfill the request immediately, and some may inform systems to acquire the necessary resources. This method is considered the entrypoint of the provisioning workflow.
